The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Jawan fire injures boy

 FARHANA KALAM

 Gaya, Jan. 19: A teenaged boy of Manpur locality here was injured when a CRPF jawan opened fire here today. 

 According to local residents, the jawan shot at a truck driver following an altercation between the two near the Mufassil police station crossing. The bullet missed the target and hit the teenager, Ravi, who was standing nearby, in his head. 

 Sources in Magadh Medical College and Hospital said they referred the boy to Patna as he was in a critical state.

 Gaya subdivisional officer B.K. Srivastava said the firing was accidental, as the jawan, pulled the trigger by mistake. A case was being registered against him, the SDO added.

 Irate residents of the locality gheraoed Mufassil police station demanding the arrest of the jawan. 




